      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification provided for turbulence model and hemolysis constitutive model selection relative to COU physics.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was selected without documented comparison to alternative constitutive models (e.g., Arora, Taskin). Turbulence model selection rationale is absent. Model form factor not assessed at required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameter distributions defined and documented for all uncertain inputs entering the Monte Carlo UQ analysis.",
      "rationale": "Distributions were assigned to 11 uncertain input parameters including viscosity, hematocrit, and pump rotational speed. Distribution types and parameters are documented in the UQ protocol. However, correlation structure among inputs was not characterized, limiting the completeness of the input characterization. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 4."
    },
